Seventy-four different taxa of invertebrates were identified during surveys around Clipperton (Table S1). Taxa were grouped into order or the lowest possible taxonomic resolution for analyses, resulting in thirty high-level taxonomic categories. More than half of these higher-level taxa (52%) had a maximum depth of 310 m or less (Fig. 2). Most of these shallow groups had narrow depth ranges (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
